{ The following lists the relevant chapters for 1...d5 players.  The repertoire clashes are detailedhere.  The 50 most important lines can be found in theQuickstarter. }
1. d4 d5 2. Nf3
{ 2.Bf4  The London system is covered inchapter 7.   2.Bg5  The Pseudo-Trompowsky is covered inchapter 3.   2.Nc3  Nf6  3.Bf4  The Jobava Attack is covered inchapter 6.   3.Bg5  the Veresov is covered inchapter 5.   Against  3.e4  you can either play  3...Nxe4  which is the easiest way to punish this gambit when White starts with 2. Nc3. It is covered inchapter 10 on the Hübsch Gambit.   OR instead play  3...dxe4  which transposes to the Blackmar-Diemer Gambit, covered inchapter 9.   2.e4  The Blackmar-Diemer Gambit is covered inchapter 9.   2.e3  Nf6  3.Bd3  c5  4.c3  Nc6  5.f4  The Stonewall is covered inchapter 1.   5.Nf3  is a version of the Colle that is also covered inchapter 1.   2.a3  The Prie attack is covered in chapter 1.   2.g3  Nf6  3.Nf3  transposes to g3 system, covered via the 2. Nf3 3. g3 move order.   Rare options such as  2.f4  ,  2.b4  ,  2.b3  ,  2.c3  ,  2.f3  and  2.Nd2  are covered inchapter 1. }
2... Nf6 3. Bg5
{ The Torre is covered inchapter 4.   3.e3  The Colle system is covered inchapter 2.   3.c3  is also covered inchapter 2.   3.g3  The g3 system is covered inchapter 8.   3.Bf4  is another way to reach the London system, which is covered inchapter 7. }
