8. g4 { is premature. After } 8... h5 9. h3
{ 9.gxh5  Rxh5⩱  is obviously better for Black. } 9... Nb6
{ when White is in an awkward pin along the h-file. The pressure on the g4 pawn forces White to release the tension with }
10. gxh5 Rxh5 11. O-O-O Bd6
{ Black is clearly better. White's pawn on h3 is a big target and we can simply complete development with ...Qe7, ...Bd7, and ...O-O-O. }
