{ Taking full control over the center. The c5 pawn isn't running away and while has no way of holding onto it. }
9. c3
{ is imprecise but a good illustration of how easily Black can take over.   Better is  9.Bg5  Be6  when  10.Qc1?!   10.Bxf6  is necessary to maintain the balance.  Nbd7  11.Bh6  a5⩱  gave Black a significant advantage in 0-1 @@StartBracket@@30@@EndBracket@@ Dresen,U @@StartBracket@@2360@@EndBracket@@ -Gutman,L @@StartBracket@@2460@@EndBracket@@ / Wuppertal 1986/CBM 001, which he converted into a full point. }
