Na6 11. Bg5 { 11.Be3  gets hit by  11...Ng4⩱ } 11... Be6
{ with the idea ...Ne4. Black will pick up the c5 pawn and retain full control over the center, granting him a slight and long lasting advantage.   A sample continuation is  11...Be6  12.Ne1  Ne4  13.Be3  Rfe8  14.Nd3  Nf6  with the idea ...Ng4.  15.h3  Nd7⩱  followed by ...Rad8 and ...Bf8. Black will recoup the c5 pawn with the upper hand. }
