1. d4 d5 2. e3
{ The Grand Prie Attack with  2.a3  is covered at theend of the chapter. It's a relatively uncommon continuation with only 200+ OTB games.   Rare options such as  2.f4  ,  2.b4  ,  2.b3  and  2.Nd2  are also addressed.   2.c3  ,  2.f3  and  2.g3  have little independent value and will transpose to other parts of the course. The exact transpositions are marked in the respective informational variations. }
2... Nf6 3. Bd3 c5 4. c3 Nc6
{ In this chapter, we are going to examine   the Stonewall system with  5.f4  . This is not a very popular  d4  system as it has only been played in 700+ OTB games.   Apart from the Stonewall, White can also transpose into the Colle system with  5.Nf3  which has been essayed in 100+ OTB games. This is a particularly poor version as it allows us to develop our bishop outside the pawn chain with  5...Bg4 }
