{ Covers the c6 knight. Black will develop with ...Bf5 and ...Qd7 next. } 7.
Nf3 Bf5 8. O-O Qd7 9. Nc3 a6 { Breaks the pin. } 10. Be2 g5
{ starts an attack against White's king. This is possible because the center is locked and White's pieces are very passive. Black can follow up with ...Ng6 and ...h5, and later decide where to place his king. Both ...Kf7 or ...O-O-O are possible depending on how White proceeds. }
