1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4
{ The Jobava Attack, named after the strong Georgian GM Baadur Jobava. This variation has also been called the Jobava-Prie Attack in honor of GM Éric Prié, who used to annotate the d4 systems column for Chesspublishing. Lichess calls it the Rapport-Jobava Attack since super-GM Richard Rapport has also played it extensively. Chess.com and 365chess.com refer to it as the Chigorin Variation. Finally, GM Simon Williams in his Chessable course called it the Jobava London System.  Jobava racked up quite a score a few years ago but has largely given it up. The reason for this is there are multiple systems where Black is very comfortable, such as 3...c5, 3...g6, and 3...a6. }
3... e6
{ is my recommendation and one of the most challenging systems. The idea is to quickly play ...Bb4 @@StartBracket@@or ...Bd6@@EndBracket@@. }
4. Nb5 { The only serious move in my opinion. } 4... Na6
{ may look awkward but is perfectly fine. We parry White's threat of Nxc7 and are ready to kick back his knight with ...c6 after we develop our kingside. }
5. e3 Be7 6. Nf3 O-O 7. a3
{ was played by Jobava 4 times but Stockfish doesn't rate it very highly. White's idea is to break with c4 without allowing ...Bb4+. }
7... c5
{ Black can also play  7...c6  8.Nc3  and only now  8...c5  However, one of the consequences of White's 8th move is that the knight on b5 is now short on squares, which we are going to try and exploit in the future. As such, there is no need to kick White's knight back with 7...c6 before playing ...c5. }
8. c3
{ This position was reached in the game ½-½  (38)  Jobava,B  (2687)  -Iturrizaga Bonelli,E  (2662)  Linares 2017. Here Black missed the opportunity to go after White's dark-squared bishop with }
8... Nh5 9. Be5 f6 10. Bg3 Nxg3
{ is a good moment to capture on g3. We're planning on going ...c4 next when White's knight on b5 will be short on squares. }
11. hxg3 c4
{ gave Black the bishop pair and the advantage in the correspondence game 0-1  (58)  Duvette,M  (2069)  -Weseman,G  (2057)  ICCF email 2018. Black has the two bishops and can reroute his knight with ...Nb8-c6. White's knight on b5 is short on squares and can be kicked back with ...a6 afterward. }
*

