9. Bd3 c5 { Our usual pawn break. } 10. O-O Nb4
{ hits the bishop and prepares to reroute the knight to c6. } 11. Be2 Nc6 12.
Ne5 Nd7 { sends White's knight packing. The pawn on h4 is also under fire. }
13. Nf3
{ Worse is  13.Nxc6  bxc6  14.Bg3  Bf6⩱  followed by ...Ba6 with a slight advantage. }
13... a6
{ Black is very comfortable and can easily take over if White is not careful. A logical next move is ...Qd8 hitting the pawn on h4. Black can then look to expand on the queenside with ...b5. }
