7. cxd5 exd5 8. Nc3
{ 8.dxc5  is harmless. After  8...Bxc5  9.Bd3  Nc6  10.O-O  d4=  Black enjoys an easy game.   8.Bd3  can also be met with  8...c4  9.Bc2  b5↑ }
8... c4
{ is rare but very interesting. It deprives White's bishop of the d3 square. The plan is to complete development with ... Be6 and ...Nbd7 and then expand on the queenside with ...a6 + ...b5. }
9. Be2 { is also possible. } 9... a6 10. O-O
{ once White castles short we can capture the bishop with } 10... Bxg3 11. hxg3
b5
{ Next up are ...Qe7, ...Bb7, and ...Nd7 taking full control over the e4 and e5 squares. This prevents White from breaking with e4, while we can focus on expanding on the queenside. }
