7. Nc3 { This is White's most popular option on move 7. } 7... cxd4 8. exd4
{ gives us the possibility of leaving White with an isolated pawn on d4. } 8...
dxc4 9. Bxc4 Nc6 10. O-O
{ Once White castles  (meaning there's no longer a rook on h1)  , it's usually a good moment to chop on g3 with }
10... Bxg3 11. hxg3 b6 12. Qd2
{ 12.a3  has also been tried.  12...Bb7  13.Rc1  improves over the game ½-½ Popovic, M @@StartBracket@@2419@@EndBracket@@ - Muratovic, E @@StartBracket@@2271@@EndBracket@@ 2007. After  13...Rc8  14.Qd3  Qc7  15.Ba2  Rfd8=  Black has a good game. }
12... Bb7
{ followed by ...Rc8 gives Black excellent play. The d4 pawn is a target and White lacks the typical activity that compensates for the isolani. }
