14... Nc5 15. exd5 Nxd3+
{ 15...e4  is also possible but riskier. Best play by both sides results in a perpetual after  16.Nxe4  Nfxe4  17.Bxe4  f5  18.d6    Rxe4  19.Rxe4  fxe4  20.Ng5  h6  21.Qc4+  Kh8  22.Nf7+  Kh7  23.b4  Nd3+  24.Rxd3    exd3  25.Qe4+  Kg8  26.Qe8+  Kh7  27.Ng5+  hxg5  28.Qh5+  Kg8  29.Qe8+=  There is obviously no need to remember all of this. }
