{ 20.d6  is playing with fire. After  20...Bxg4  White can still maintain the balance but has to play like an engine. Best play by both sides goes  21.d7  Red8  22.Rxg4  hxg4  23.Nxe5  Qf5  24.Qd4  Qf6  25.Qe3  Qe6  26.Qd4  Qf6= }
20... Qf1+ 21. Rd1 Qf2
{ with a draw by repetition, a typical outcome nowadays when both sides play perfectly.   'Long analysis, wrong analysis' is a famous Bent Larsen quote. Even though it does not apply here, feel free to pause this line if it's too complicated @@StartBracket@@and recall that 10...Qb6 is my main recommendation@@EndBracket@@. }
