[White "7. London (1...d5 and 1...Nf6 2...e6)"]
[Black "5. Ne5 [8...Nbd7 alternative]"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 { The London system } 2... Nf6 3. e3 e6 4. Nf3 Bd6
{ immediately fighting for the e5 square and clearing the way for ...O-O. } 5.
Ne5
{ immediately establishing the knight on e5 is one of those early deviations meant to avoid theory. The following variation is instructive in showing how to deal with White's knight. }
5... O-O 6. Nd2
{ Alternatively  6.Bd3  can be met with  6...c5  7.c3  Qc7  8.Bg3  White delays the development of the b1 knight, opting to reinforce the e5 knight with f2-f4 instead.  8...Nbd7   Also possible is  8...c4  9.Bc2  Nc6=  The knight is better placed on c6 than on d7 to support the ...b7-b5-b4 queenside expansion.  9.f4  Cements the knight on e5 but critically weakens the e4 square, which Black can immediately exploit with  9...Ne4=  with good play. This move is only possible because White's knight is still on b1. }
6... c5 7. c3 Qc7
{ Precise. We first protect the bishop on d6 and then follow up with ...Nbd7 to challenge White's knight. }
8. Bd3 Nbd7 9. Ndf3
{ White is in time to reinforce the knight on e5 but now all his pieces are tied up in this task. As such, it's the perfect time for Black to expand on the queenside with }
9... c4
{ A timely moment to release the tension in the center. We're ready to quickly follow up with ...b5 and ...Bb7. This will prevent White from breaking with e3-e4, which is his typical counter to ...c4. }
10. Bc2 b5
{ with ideas of ...a5 and ...b4.   A sample continuation is  11.h4  b4  12.h5  h6  13.g4  bxc3  14.bxc3  Ne4  15.g5  Nxc3  16.Qc1  hxg5  17.Nxg5  Nxe5  18.dxe5  Bb4  19.Kf1  Ne4  with all to play for.   Also possible is  11.g4  Ne4!  12.g5  b4  13.Bxe4  dxe4  Now  14.Nxd7  is White's only good continuation. After  14...Bxd7  15.Ne5  f6  16.gxf6  Rxf6  17.O-O  bxc3  18.bxc3  Raf8=  Black has good play.  The doubled-edged play after 11. g4 led me to mark 8...Nbd7 as an alternative line and instead suggest8...a5 as my main recommendation. }
