8. Bxc4 c5 { Immediately challenging White's center. } 9. dxc5
{ creates a symmetrical pawn structure where Black has no problems. For example, after }
9... Qxc5 10. Qd4 Qxd4
{ Black can also keep the queens on the board with  10...Qe7!?  11.O-O  Nc6  12.Qf4  e5=  with good prospects. }
11. Nxd4 Bd7 { followed by ...Nc6 and ...Rac8 is very comfortable. } *

