{ Having defended the c4 pawn, we're now ready to plant our knight on e4.  Alternatively }
16. Qd2 Ne4 17. Bxe4 dxe4
{ followed by ...f6 gives Black the upper hand.   A sample continuation is  18.h3  f6  19.Ng4  Bc6  rerouting the bishop to d5.  20.Rec1  Bd5⩱  followed by ...Rfb8 with good play on the queenside. White's knight on g4 is completely misplaced. }
