{ This pawn break is very effective. Both of our e-pawns are under attack but capturing any of them is awful for White. }
6. Be3 exd4 7. Bxd4
{ 7.Qxd4  is obviously a bad idea. After  7...Qxd4  8.Bxd4  Nc6  9.Bb5  Bf5  10.O-O-O  O-O-O∓  White is simply a pawn down. Note that  11.Bxc6  bxc6  12.Bxa7?  fails to restore material equality as after  12...Rxd1  13.Kxd1  c5  White is now forced to give back up a pawn with  14.b4  to save the bishop. Following  14...cxb4  15.Bf2  Bd6−+  Black has a decisive advantage. }
