e3 { is very strong. White is already dead lost. The point is that... } 13.
fxe3
{ The alternatives aren't much better.   13.f3  can be answered with  13...h5  undermining White's pawn structure.   Covering the pawn with  13.Nh3  is strongly met by  13...e5!  sacrificing a pawn so that after  14.dxe5  Be7  Black can play ...Bh4 without White being able to retreat his dark-squared bishop to g3. Black is winning.   Finally, blocking the 2nd rank with  13.Ne2  is answered with  13...exf2  14.Kxf2  Nf6  15.h3  h5−+  with a decisive advantage. }
13... Be4 { ...wins White's rook! } *

