{ The Stonewall system. White takes firm control over the e5 square with f2-f4. White wants to plant a knight on e5 and then start a kingside attack with Qe1-h4. However, I'm sure the bishop on c1 isn't too happy with the way White arranged his pawns.  When Black has already played ...e6, White's Stonewall system gains slightly in strength. This is because we no longer have the option of developing the light-squared bishop outside the pawn chain. That being said, it's still very unambitious and Black can obtain a great game in a number of ways. }
