e5 { Our pawn break is in and I'd much rather be Black here. } 10. g4
{ was played in an engine vs engine match all the way back in 2011. } 10...
exd4
{ is a very interesting sacrifice, exploiting White's lack of development. }
11. gxh5
{ 11.cxd4  Nhf6=  is more than fine for Black. In fact, White may soon be wishing his g-pawn was back on g2. }
11... dxe3 12. fxe3 Rxe3+ { comes with check! } 13. Kf2 Bh6
{ keeps the rook on e3. Next up is ...Nf6 bringing more pieces towards White's king. }
14. Kg2 Nf6 15. hxg6 hxg6 16. Rg1 Bf5
