Ne8
{ followed by ...Nd6 and ...f6 gives Black an excellent game. We can easily take over if White is not accurate as the following sample lines illustrate. }
10. Ndf3
{ may seem natural reinforcing the e5 knight, but is an inaccuracy.   10.Qe2  Nd6  11.dxc5?!  is a mistake on account of  11...Ne4  12.Nxc6  Qxc6  13.Nxe4  dxe4  14.Bc2  Be6⩱  Black will pick up the c5 pawn with ...Bd5 and ...Rc8 next. }
10... c4 11. Bc2 f6 { boots White's knight from the e5 square. } 12. Nxc6 Qxc6
{ followed by ...Nd6 and ...Bf5 gives Black the upper hand. } *

