{ is White's idea. It would work if not for the novel } 8... Nc6
{ improving over the game 1-0 @@StartBracket@@54@@EndBracket@@ Dupsky,L @@StartBracket@@2227@@EndBracket@@-Vass,L @@StartBracket@@2158@@EndBracket@@ Hungary 2010. The point is that }
9. Nxe4 { is strongly met with } 9... b5 10. Qc2
{ is the only way to hold on to the knight on e4 but it walks straight into a devastating pin with }
10... Bf5 { White is forced to further weaken his position with } 11. f3 Bg7
12. Qd3 Bxe4 13. Qxe4 Qxe4 14. fxe4 Rb8
{ is clearly better for Black. White's pawn structure with doubled e-pawns is awful. If that weren't already enough, Black is ahead in development and ready to undermine White's queenside with ...b4. }
