8. e3 Nxc5 9. Nge2
{ 9.Be5  can be answered with  9...Qb6=  starting active play on the queenside. Black is threatening ...Nfe4.   9.g4  is well met by  9...Qb6  10.Nge2  Re8∓  with the idea ...e5.   Finally  9.Nxd5??  is a blunder. After  9...Nxd5  10.Qxd5  Qa5  White is in big trouble with ...Be6 coming. For example  11.a3  Be6  12.Qd2  Bxb2!  crashes through!  13.Kxb2  Na4  14.Kc1  Nc3+−  White is busted. }
