3... Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. b3
{ This early fianchetto is much less popular than  5.O-O  or  5.c4  the reason being that Black can immediately strike with }
5... c5 { undermining White's center. } 6. Bb2 cxd4 7. O-O
{ is similar to6. O-O. Black should take over the center with } 7... d5 8. Bxd4
Nc6 9. Bb2 Qc7
{ White cannot allow ...e5 and should immediately strike in the center with }
