5... d6 { is the move King's Indian players should make. } 6. Nbd2
{ is the 6th moves popular option, intending to expand in the center with e2-e4.   6.c4  transposes to a mainline in the King's Indian, which is outside the scope of this course. }
6... Re8
{ is rare but one of the top suggestions by the neural network engines. The idea is simple: Black wants to break with ...e7-e5. }
